President Biden held a Cabinet meeting to discuss the progress of investing in America and the steps each agency is taking to continue this progress. He highlighted the bipartisan budget agreement that reduces the deficit by nearly $1 trillion and protects Social Security, Medicare, Medicaid, and veterans care. The president also mentioned the economic progress, such as attracting $470 billion in private investment, fighting climate change, and lowering costs for prescription drugs. Additionally, he announced the launch of a new website called Invest.gov, which showcases infrastructure and private sector investment projects across the country. During a brief press interaction, President Biden emphasized that the U.S. will continue to support Ukraine in the face of Russian aggression and stated that his statement on the anniversary of D-Day is forthcoming.